item.description: Quentin Tarantino looking content with life in 1994. He had a nice cigar, Uma Thurman on his arm and a VHS tape in his hand. It doesn't get much better than that.

item.title: [+1649] Franken Calms Down Health Care Opponents (VIDEO)
item.description: While coverage of the health care reform debate has focused on yelling, booing and fistfights, not all engagements between lawmakers and constituents turn hostile. Sen. Al Franken (D-Minn.) discussed his beliefs and goals about health care reform at the Minnesota State Fair Wednesday with a group of constituents, and calmed down some who were upset

item.title: [+1204] Cop Forces Women to Stop using CPR on her Grandson. Boy Dies
item.description: They say their three-year-old grandson might have survived if a Wichita police officer hadn't made them stop CPR. Isaiah Jones drowned in his grandparents' above-ground pool last week.

item.title: [+1041] People Of Walmart, Fashion Challenged Freaks
item.description: what is it about Walmart that brings out the—how do I say this delicately?—fashion-challenged freaks. A satirical site called People of Walmart now lets you stare to your heart’s content without actually stepping inside a Walmart store.

item.title: [+974] 10 Wierd Statues
item.description: Virtual tour of the top 10 coolest statues in the world.

item.title: [+787] Bachmann: Dems Are Sabotaging Me Because I Might Become Prez
item.description: Rep. Michele Bachmann (R-MN) finally explained yesterday why Democrats don't want her in office: They're scared she'll become the first female president. "They want to make sure no women, no woman becomes president before a Democrat woman" Bachmann said.

item.title: [+739] Fox's Twitter TV Experiment Tweets Its Way to Epic Failure
item.description: When Fox revealed its plan to broadcast reruns of Fringe and Glee with a live Twitter feed overlay, I said they had to be really really careful. But Fox didn't listen. From user comments online it looks like the experiment earned itself a big FAIL.

item.title: [+736] Man...That's Low!
item.description: An RAF Harrier jet shows just how low it can get as a serviceman poses at the end of the runway.

item.title: [+718] Danny DeVito joined Twitter. His profile PIC is glorious.
item.description: I don't see a "verified" badge but I think it would be hard to dispute that this is in fact Danny DeVito using twitter. Thank you, Internet.

item.title: [+694] What happens to your online accounts after you die?
item.description: This article highlights some of the Tools for Managing Your Online Life After Death. It also tells you what happens to your online account at major places like facbook and others after you die.

item.title: [+629] Anti-Piracy Boss Confiscates Confiscated Hacker Laptop
item.description: Tim Kuik, managing director of Dutch anti-piracy gang BREIN, has publicly admitted that he’s currently using a Sony VAIO laptop previously confiscated from a ‘hacker’. Although he doesn’t elaborate on how he obtained the machine, it is hard not to conclude that it has been misappropriated.

item.title: [+593] Glenn Beck & Glenn Beck are Back
item.description: Watch Glenn Beck and his clone respond to the anti-American advertisers that pulled their ads from his show.

item.title: [+588] Man stops would-be robber with a sword
item.description: A robbery gone wrong ended when the victim upped the ante on the would-be robber by pulling a sword.

item.title: [+499] Astronomy Picture of the Day Supernova Remnant E0102-72
item.description: A different astronomy and space sciencerelated image is featured each day, along with a brief explanation.

item.title: [+493] Stay-In-School Speech Protesters - "A lot of stupid people"
item.description: JOHN HARWOOD: "I gotta’ tell you Monica, I’ve been watching politics for a long time, and this one is really over-the-top. What is shows you is there are a lot of cynical people who try to fan controversy, and let’s face it, in a country of 300 million people, there are a lot of stupid people too"

item.title: [+471] Antibodies found that prevent HIV from causing severe AIDS
item.description: After nearly two decades of futile searching for a vaccine against the AIDS virus, researchers are reporting the tantalizing discovery of antibodies that can prevent the virus from multiplying in the body and producing severe disease.

item.title: [+464] Trailer Park Boys: The Timeless Wisdom of Bubbles (PICS)
item.description: While Ricky, Randy, and J-Rock and Julian provide no dearth of one-liners and exchanges, it is the hapless Bubbles that's always held a special place in our hearts.

item.title: [+459] Ten Amazing Performances from Sesame Street
item.description: Though Sesame Street has always focused its learning programming towards children, the appearance of impressive live musical acts has remained a solid mainstay. Jim Henson was a genius.

item.title: [+426] Forced Catheterization Used In DUI Case
item.description: An Indiana man has filed a lawsuit claiming that police forcibly withdrew blood and urine from his body during a drunken driving arrest. A Breathalyzer test showed he was under the legal limit, but Officer Brian Miller doubted the findings.
